            "author_association": "MEMBER",
            "body": "`stdin=\"pipe\"` is a bit misleading, it just means stdin is connected instead of being closed (which is a pipe for a normal job and a tty for a termopen() job).\r\n\r\nWe will need a separate option for this usecase. I think we should allow to open a PTY without any job running it it, and then run `jobstart()` with the stdout redirected to the PTY. then you will get two separate channel ids for PTY input and process input.",
